I. Aggregate functions: 
COUNT, SUM, AVG, MAX, MIN, VARIANCE, STDDEV

SELECT COUNT(column) newcolumn
FROM table 
WHERE ...;

II. 
GROUP BY
HAVING

III. Date and Time functions:
ADD_MONTHS(column, n), LASTDAY(column), MONTHS_BETWEEN(ENDDATE, STARTDATE), NEW_TIME(column, zone1, zone2)
NEXT_DAY(date, 'FRIDAY'), SYSDATE


IV. Arithmetric functions: f(column)
SIGN, ABS, CEIL, FLOOR, COS, COSH, SIN, SINH, TAN, TANH, SQRT, EXP, LN, LOG(column, n), MOD(column1, column2)
POW(column1, column2)	// if negative number in column1, column2 has to be integer, use CEIL or FLOOR


V. Characer functions: f(column)
CHR, INITCAP, LOWER, UPPER, LENGTH
CONCAT(column1, column2), SUBSTR(column, n1, n2)
LPAD(column, n, '*'), RPAD, LTRIM(column, 'c'), RTRIM, REPLACE(column, 'ab', 'cd')
TRANSLATE(column, 'abcd','efgh')

VI. Conversion functions: f(column)
TO_CHAR, TO_NUMBER

VII. Miscellaneous functions
GREATEST, LEAST, USER


